    "\n",
    "## 🗣️ Discuss: In Your Group\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.ltblue-container .thirtyfourpt-font}\n",
    "🎯 **Checkpoint 2. a:**\n",
    "<br><br>\n",
    "[**Q1:** How tall will our tower be if we use **100 cubes**?]{.fragment}  \n",
    "<br>\n",
    "[**Q2:** Your friend argues that the tower will be 99 inches tall. What would you tell him? Why?]{.fragment}\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Scenario 2: Cheap Uncle Bob\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.fourtyeightpt-font .incremental}\n",
    "- We want to build a much taller tower than our current 10\" one, but we ran out of 1\" cubes.\n",
    "- 🎉 Uncle Bob volunteers to make us more cubes — cheaper!\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Scenario 2: Cheap Uncle Bob\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    "Oh no! Uncle Bob's cubes are all slightly different heights!\n",
    "\n",
    "![](images/green-cubes-multsizing.png){fig-align=\"center\" width=\"35%\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🗣️ Discuss: In Your Group\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.ltblue-container .thirtyfourpt-font}\n",
    "🎯 **Checkpoint 2. b:**\n",
    "<br><br>\n",
    "How will Uncle Bob's new cubes affect our tower height predictions?\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "# The Case for Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Case for Regression\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns}\n",
    "::: {.column}\n",
    "![True with perfectly 1\" cubes](images/cube-plot-11-noregline.png){width=90%}\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.activity-text .column}\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Case for Regression\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns}\n",
    "::: {.column}\n",
    "![Reality with Uncle Bob's cubes](images/cube-plot-unclebob.png){width=90%}\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.activity-text .column}\n",
    "Bob's cubes saved us money, but now tower heights are all over the place.  <br><br>\n",
    "We need a better way to predict.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "## How Do We Fit Our Line?\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns}\n",
    "::: {.column}\n",
    "![Very clear line with perfect cubes](images/cube-plot-11.png)\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.column}\n",
    "![Need **regression** — the mathematical best-fit line](images/cube-plot-unclebob-regline.png)\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Smokey Buoy: Regression\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.fourtyeightpt-font .incremental}\n",
    "- The buoy also uses **regression** to predict nitrate levels.\n",
    "- Let's learn a bit more about this!\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "# 🔬<br>Regression Activity — Pt. I:<br>RGB and Scatterplots\n",
    "\n",
    "## Averaging RGB\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.activity-text}\n",
    "In Workshop #2, we learned how computers \"see\" color through RGB values. The buoy takes **all the pixels** for each test pad and finds their **mean**.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns style=\"display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;\"}\n",
    "::: {.column style=\"display:flex; justify-content:center;\"}\n",
    "![](images/Red_Pixels.png){style=\"height:300px; width:auto; object-fit:contain;\"}\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.column style=\"display:flex; justify-content:center;\"}\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Averaging RGB\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.activity-text}\n",
    "In Workshop #2, we learned how computers \"see\" color through RGB values. The buoy takes **all the pixels** for each test pad and finds their **mean**.\n",
