   "source": [
    "## Activity Pt. V: Predict New Concentrations\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.gray-container .fourtyeightpt-font}\n",
    "**Materials Needed:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- 💻 [RGB Applet V2](https://appalachianaicorps.org/modules/water-quality/RGB-Applet-2.html){target=\"_blank\"}\n",
    "- Three Additional \"Nitrate Test Pad\" Cards\n",
    "- Handout / Pencil\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Activity Pt. V: Predict New Concentrations\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.fourtyeightpt-font}\n",
    "1. Use the applet to find the R, G, or B value for the new cards (per your group).\n",
    "2. Use the graphing tool to **predict the nitrate concentration (ppm)**.\n",
    "3. Record these predictions on your handout.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "# Understanding R²\n",
    "\n",
    "## How Good Is Our Model? R²\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.activity-text}\n",
    "**R²** (R-squared) tells us how well our regression line fits the data — like a report card:\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "| R² value | What it means |\n",
    "|----------|---------------|\n",
    "| Close to **100%** | Line fits very well — predictions will be accurate |\n",
    "| Around **70–90%** | A reasonably strong fit |\n",
    "| Close to **0%** | Line barely fits — predictions won't be reliable |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Calculate Your R² Value\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.dkorange-container .thirtyfourpt-font}\n",
    "Click ▶️ **Run Code** to calculate your model's R² value.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "r_squared = calculate_rsquared(color_data, nitrate_ppm, slope, intercept)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"R² = {r_squared * 100:.1f}%\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "## Calculate Your R² Value\n",
    "<hr>\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.dkorange-container .thirtyfourpt-font}\n",
    "Click ▶️ **Run Code** to calculate your model's R² value.\n",
    ":::"
   ]
  },
